<P>
   ROYAL-OPERA (London) _ For the last three years the Royal Opera
House has been a soap opera made for the tabloids. But an American,
Michael Kaiser, the former executive director of the American
Ballet Theater, arrived here in mid-November to sort out the
warring British, and now, just 10 weeks later, there are signs that
peace is breaking out. By Alan Riding.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos [NYT7,8) have been sent to NYT photo clients.)
