<HEADLINE>
U.S. DODGES `GROUP OF DEATH'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN JOSE _ Most observers agreed that the United States women's
national team avoided the so-called ``Group of Death'' following
the announcement of the 1999 Women's World Cup Draw at halftime of
the FIFA World All-Stars' 2-1 victory over the U.S. team at Spartan
Stadium on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   But when the third women's world championships begin this summer
in the United States, the U.S. will likely have to fight a little
harder than it wanted to reach the second round.
</P>
<P>
   Denmark, the only European team to beat the U.S. in the 1990's;
Nigeria, who claimed its third consecutive African title by
outscoring opponents 28-0 in qualifying; and Korea joined the
American team in Group A of the four-group, 16-team tournament.
</P>
<P>
   The U.S., the inaugural World Cup champions in 1991 and
third-place finishers in 1995, will open with Denmark on June 19 at
Giants Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Nigeria and Korea are two teams the U.S. has never faced.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a draw that I would say is unknown because I don't know
anything about Nigeria or Korea,'' U.S. coach Tony DiCicco said.
``Nigeria is the first seed from Africa, North Korea has stretched
China in two games and we all know how tough China is. Denmark, of
course, is one of the best teams in Europe.
</P>
<P>
   ``We knew we would get a draw that wouldn't be an easy draw and
certainly we don't think this is an easy draw. We will have to play
better than we did tonight to reach the second round.''
</P>
<P>
   U.S. forward Tiffany Milbret is a little nervous about facing a
pair of teams she's never seen before.
</P>
<P>
   ``Personally, I'm a little scared of unknown teams,'' she said.
``You don't know how they are going to play really, and often those
types of teams are scrappy teams. And scrappy teams' strengths tend
to match up against our weaknesses pretty well.''
</P>
<P>
   Brazil, believed to be the best of the non-seeded teams, joined
Italy and top-seeded Germany in Group C, dubbed the ``Group of
Death.''
</P>
<P>
   In group B, top-seeded and defending World Cup champion Norway
drew Japan, Canada and Russia in its group. In group D, Australia,
Ghana and Sweden joined China, the final top seed of the four
groups.
</P>
<P>
   The Rose Bowl will host the World Cup final July 10 and also a
first-round doubleheader on June 20 with Germany-Italy and
Korea-Nigeria.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
