   4. JEWEL, by Bret Lott. (Washington Square/Pocket, $14.)
</P>
<P>
   The life of a poor Mississippi woman is strained
</P>
<P>
   and enriched by her daughter, who has Down syndrome.
</P>
<P>
   5. CHARMING BILLY, by Alice McDermott. (Delta,
</P>
<P>
   $12.95.) At a party to celebrate a man's
</P>
<P>
   memory, many secrets of the past come to life.
</P>
<P>
   6. WHERE THE HEART IS, by Billie Letts. (Warner, $12.)
</P>
<P>
   A pregnant teen-ager, left stranded in a small
</P>
<P>
   Oklahoma town, finds help and caring from its
</P>
<P>
   inhabitants.
</P>
<P>
   7. TOM CLANCY'S NET FORCE, created by Tom Clancy and
</P>
<P>
   Steve Pieczenik. (Berkeley, $7.99.) In 2010, federal
</P>
<P>
   agents combat terrorist sabotage of defense and
</P>
<P>
   intelligence computer systems.
