<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ My son scares me half to
death and comes up with ``Sorry.'' He's never been a coordinated
kid, and that hasn't changed much. But stumbling into adulthood,
he's made me proud; him and his girlfriend recently became engaged.
(Elizabeth Schuett, a teacher and writer in Gibsonburg, Ohio,
writes twice a week for Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ One
way for Congress to regain a few of the approval points it
squandered on the impeachment debacle would be to do something
about air travel. To talk to a frequent flier is to open yourself
to hair-raising tales of hardy souls braving discomfort,
dislocation and airline treatment that can border on false
imprisonment. Here's my version of the Passenger Bill of Rights.
(Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GEEWAX-Y2K-COLUMN _ This column will not move this week.
(Geewax, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
