<P>
   NY-FASHION _ NEW YORK _ Fall fashion week '99 continues.
Designers showing: Carolina Herrera, Badgley Mischka, Mary
McFadden, Betsy Johnson and BCBG/Max Azria. inside. (Walton,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   NY-FASHION-BUZZ _ NEW YORK _ Runway notes and scene sidebar.
(Walton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   GENEAOLOGY _ Inspired by memoirs like ``Angela's Ashes'' and the
fear that the memories of their parents' and grandparents'
generation will die with them, baby boomers are taking steps to
preserve their family histories. They're writing family memoirs,
taping parents telling favorite stories, and other measures to hold
onto a piece of their past. Many employ entrepreneurs who've tapped
onto a gold mine - a growing market for family stories, legends and
geneologies, many of which turn into books. There's even a
``roots'' service in Atlanta with its own web site. (Hendrick,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 45-50. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMERQ&AMP;A _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Consumer Q&AMP;A. This week: Keeping
Oneida silverware stain-free and other consumer questions. (Greig,
Austin American-Statesman) (l, a) MOVED
</P>
