<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Bob
McCarthy at the Daily News, (818) 713-3665. 
 
 
PASSING-GLORY (Los Angeles) _ In 1965, Jesuit High School's boys
basketball team in New Orleans was 29-1 while St. Augustine High
School's team across town was 30-0. While white and black high
schools didn't play one another back then, an informal game was
arranged and the matchup is the basis for the TNT movie ``Passing
Glory,'' written by Harold Sylvester, who played and starred in
that contest. By David Bloom. 
 
 
LATRAVIATA-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ Review of Guiseppe Verdi's
ever-popular ``La Traviata,'' which arrived in Los Angeles Sunday.
By Reed Johnson. 
 
 
AWARDS-SITES (Los Angeles) _ Browse the Oscar.com site to be in the
know about this year's Academy Awards or check out some other
awards competitions for new media. By David Bloom. 

