<P>
   CAR-DAYTONA (Daytona Beach, Fla.) _ The yellow flag waved on lap
175, and for those lucky enough to avoid the messy 12 car wreck on
the previous lap, there was a tough decision to be made: Stay out
or come in? At the time, Rusty Wallace was leading Sunday's Daytona
500. He radioed his crew chief Robin Pemberton to discuss strategy.
Stay out on worn Goodyears, or come in for some new ones? Since the
car was handling OK, Wallace and Pemberton chose to stay out.
Wallace's teammate, Jeremy Mayfield, stayed out too. But their
gamble didn't work. By Tarik El-Bashir.
</P>
