</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ An accused killer on death row in
Chicago recently freed by new evidence uncovered by college
students that he was wrongly sentenced has become a symbol for the
cause of outlawing capital punishment. But execution is the
appropriate punishment for premeditated killers who murder at will.
By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
