<P>
   LA-VALLEY-HOMES (Los Angeles) _ After setting a hot pace during
1998, San Fernando Valley's residential real estate market cooled
considerably during January as single-family home sales fell 12.6
percent from year-ago levels, a trade group said Monday. Prices,
though, continued trending up with the median price rising to
$190,000, or a gain of 8.9 percent from January 1998. By Gregory J.
Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   ROMAN-RESIGNS (Los Angeles) _ Phil Roman, the founder and
chairman of Film Roman, has resigned from his animation studio.
Although Film Roman has won numerous awards and is the pen behind
such TV successes as ``The Simpsons'' and ``King of the Hill,'' the
publicly-held company has never been able to reap the rewards of
its successes because its never owned the rights to a successful
animation project. By Dave McNary.
