conspiring to steal cemetery ornaments. ``The thieves are in
jail,'' said Patout, currently out on bail. It was in Patout's
courtyard that detectives seized two funerary statues, including a
$50,000 Madonna. The New Orleans police say they were part of a
cache of more than 200 urns, angels and Blessed Mothers plundered
by thieves last year from the above-ground tombs and sarcophagi
that populate New Orlean's ``cities of the dead.'' The FBI has
entered the investigation, which has moved on to Los Angeles and
may soon include New York. By Patricia Leigh Brown. 2,000 words.
