<P>
   MEXICO-CLINTON (Merida, Mexico) _ Leaving little doubt that he
intends to report later this month to Congress that Mexico is a
reliable partner in the drug war, President Clinton says that
``Mexico should not be penalized'' for its handling of its
anti-narcotics campaigns. With President Ernesto Zedillo listening
at his side during a speech capping a 23-hour working visit here,
Clinton praises what he characterizes as the sincerity and valor of
Mexico's anti-drug initiatives. By James Bennet. (We plan to move
the story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
