</P>
<P>
   CEMETERY-ROBBERIES (New Orleans) _ On an atmospherically moody
day, Peter Patout, an antiques dealer, was cosseted in his Bourbon
Street home, where he gave his version of the crime: conspiring to
steal cemetery ornaments. ``The thieves are in jail,'' said Patout,
currently out on bail. It was in Patout's courtyard that detectives
seized two funerary statues, including a $50,000 Madonna. The New
Orleans police say the statues they were part of a cache of more
than 200 urns, angels and Blessed Mothers plundered by thieves last
year from the above-ground tombs and sarcophagi that populate New
Orlean's ``cities of the dead.'' The FBI has entered the
