President Nixon's pugnacious defender and domestic policy chief and
who went to prison for his role in the Watergate scandals, died on
Sunday at his home in Atlanta. He was 73. Ehrlichman had been
suffering from diabetes for about a year, his son Tom of Seattle
said. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
