<HEADLINE>
PESTICIDE COMPANY DISPUTES SERIOUSNESS OF CONTAMINATION
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies ENVIRONMENTAL-ACTIVIST) c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Elf Atochem officials strongly disagree with the opinions and
conclusions that were espoused by Mark O'Connor about the
seriousness of arsenic contamination in Bryan, Texas.
</P>
<P>
   ``We in no way want to show any disrespect to the deceased,''
said Peter McCarthy, vice president of Elf Atochem North America,
``because he forced us to do a lot of research, so there has been a
benefit to his work. But in truth, our research shows that he spent
his life pursuing things that were just plain wrong.''
</P>
<P>
   McCarthy referred to recent Elf Atochem studies on the effects
of arsenic inhalation, prompted by numerous lawsuits. The studies,
released to the Fort Worth Star-Telegram but not yet public, show
that the company has measured the effects of inhalation of arsenic
in rats to determine if it affected their offspring. The study
concluded that only when the rats inhaled enough arsenic to kill
them would it have any effect.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our study clearly shows that inhalation of arsenic in the
amounts we were talking about does not cause birth defects,'' said
Karen Flynn, associate general counsel of Elf Atochem North
America. ``In fact, if we had had this study when we settled the
(anencephalic babies) case in 1994, we would not have settled.''
</P>
<P>
   Flynn said the studies the company has conducted are
groundbreaking and go further than previous studies. Many studies
done on arsenic levels in drinking water suggest a correlation
between arsenic ingestion and lung or skin cancer. Other studies
have suggested a correlation between lung cancer and arsenic
inhalation, although none of these studies claims to be absolute in
its conclusions.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mainly, we would not want the people in Bryan to think there
is currently an arsenic problem still there, because there is
not,'' Flynn said.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
