<DOCNO> NYT19990215.0382 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-15 23:29 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6492 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-LAKENOT-LADN-(SLA     02-15 0359
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKENOT-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HORRY OUT OF HOSPITAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ Los Angeles Lakers forward Robert Horry was
discharged from the hospital Monday, 24 hours after being diagnosed
with an irregular heartbeat, and he could be playing again as soon
as tonight's game against the Charlotte Hornets.
</P>
<P>
   After experiencing chest pains Sunday, Horry spent the night at
Centinela Medical Center, where he underwent a battery of tests
under the supervision of team internist Dr. John Moe, and his heart
was monitored constantly.
</P>
<P>
   ``All the tests came back within the range of normal,'' and
Horry's heartbeat has returned to normal, Lakers spokesman John
Black said.
</P>
<P>
   Horry is wearing a heart monitor and his heartbeat will be
measured when he participates in today's shootaround. If all goes
well, he will be cleared to play tonight. ``They're looking for any
irregularity in the next 24 hours,'' Black said.
</P>
<P>
   Doctors could not determine the cause for the irregular
heartbeat, though it could be related to Horry's recent bout with
an upper respiratory infection.
</P>
<P>
   The news of Horry's discharge was greeted with relief by the
team.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have been hoping and praying that nothing would be wrong
with it,'' coach Del Harris said.
</P>
<P>
   The experience put a scare into coaches and teammates, who
couldn't help but think of Hank Gathers of Loyola Marymount and
Reggie Lewis of the Boston Celtics, both of whom had heart
conditions and died playing basketball.
</P>
<P>
   ``You put your heart under a lot of stress to do this work,''
Harris said, ``and that's always in the back of your mind. . . .
Even though the guys were concerned about Robert first of all, I'm
sure everybody kind of checked their own hearts to see how they
were working. It's only natural.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Ouch report: Shaquille O'Neal did not practice with the team
but went through a workout to rehab his strained groin and is
expected to start tonight.
</P>
<P>
   Rick Fox was sent home with an upper respiratory infection but
could be available for spot minutes off the bench.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-15-99 2329EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990215.0383 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-15 23:32 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6495 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CHURCH-FIRE-1200(2TAK     02-15 0997
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CHURCH-FIRE-1200(2TAKES)-1STLD-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WINDSWEPT FIRE AT CHURCH KILLS THREE FIREFIGHTERS
</HEADLINE>
 
